articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's manufacturing activity contracted for a second straight month in November and at a quicker pace, an official factory survey showed on Thursday, suggesting more government policy support measures are needed to help shore up economic growth.
articles.title: China's factory activity contracts for second month in November

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Singapore and Zurich tied for the world's most expensive city this year, followed by Geneva, New York and Hong Kong, the Economist Intelligence Unit (EIU) said on Thursday as it cautioned that the global cost-of-living crisis was not yet over.
articles.title: Singapore, Zurich world's most expensive cities - EIU

articles.author: Kane Wu
articles.description: Asian stocks were poised to clock their strongest performance in 10 months at the end of Thursday's trading, even as most regional stock markets opened listless after mixed messages from the Fed and a similar struggle in U.S. stocks overnight.
articles.title: Asia stocks closing in on strongest month since January

articles.author: Anirban Sen, Deena Beasley
articles.description: Major U.S. health insurer Cigna (CI.N) is in merger talks with Humana (HUM.N), a source familiar with the matter said on Wednesday, a deal that would give Cigna a much greater foothold in the fast-growing market for managing federal Medicare plans for older Americans.
articles.title: US health insurers Humana, Cigna in talks to merge -source

articles.author: Lisa Richwine
articles.description: Walt Disney (DIS.N) Chief Executive Bob Iger said on Wednesday he would "definitely" step down when his current contract ends in 2026 and that the ABC broadcast network was not for sale.
articles.title: Disney CEO Iger promises 2026 exit, says ABC not for sale

articles.author: Lucia Mutikani
articles.description: The U.S. economy grew faster than initially thought in the third quarter as businesses built more warehouses and accumulated machinery equipment, but momentum appears to have since waned as higher borrowing costs curb hiring and spending.
articles.title: US third-quarter growth revised higher; corporate profits rise strongly

articles.author: Martin Coulter
articles.description: Google DeepMind has used artificial intelligence (AI) to predict the structure of more than 2 million new materials, a breakthrough it said could soon be used to improve real-world technologies.
articles.title: Google DeepMind AI reveals potential for thousands of new materials

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Mohammad Salem, Emily Rose
articles.description: International pressure grew on Israel and Hamas to extend a truce on Thursday after another exchange of hostages for Palestinian prisoners and humanitarian aid was delivered to the besieged Gaza Strip.
articles.title: Talks intensify to extend Israel-Hamas truce after more hostages, prisoners freed

articles.author: Sheila Dang
articles.title: Elon Musk curses out advertisers who left X over antisemitic content

articles.author: Kiyoshi Takenaka, Tim Kelly
articles.description: A U.S. military aircraft carrying eight people crashed into the sea in Japan on Wednesday, killing at least one crew member with the condition of at least two others hauled from waters unclear.
articles.title: US military aircraft crashes in sea off Japan, at least one dead
